fr:mainmatter.html:p:
A Borel measure \mu  on a topological space X is outer regular on a Borel set E if

\mu (E) = \inf  \left \{  \mu (W) : E \subseteq  W, \; W \text { is open}  \right \}

where W is an open set.

A Borel measure \mu  on a topological space X is inner regular on a Borel set E if

\mu (E) = \sup  \left \{  \mu (M) : M \subseteq  E, \; M \text { is compact}  \right \}

where M is a compact subset.

